# UI/UX Audit Report: Antha Tech Public Website (Mobile)

**Auditor:** UI/UX Auditor (20+ Years Experience)  
**Date:** March 9, 2026  
**Viewports Tested:** 430x932 (iPhone 14 Pro Max), 360x780 (Standard Android)

---

## 1. Executive Summary

While the desktop experience of Antha Tech is polished, the mobile adaptation currently faces several **critical usability and aesthetic issues**. The most severe issues are the **intrusive sticky social sidebar** and the **missing mobile navigation menu**, which together compromise the user's ability to read content and navigate the site.

---

## 2. Global UI/UX Issues (Shared Across All Pages)

### 🚨 Critical: Sticky Social Sidebar Overlap
- **Issue:** The vertical social media icons pinned to the left side of the screen overlap primary buttons, headings, and images on every page.
- **Impact:** High. It makes the site look broken and hinders interaction with key CTA buttons.
- **Solution:** Hide this sidebar on viewports below 768px. Move social links to the Footer or a "Share" icon in the Navbar.

### 🚨 Major: Missing Mobile Navigation
- **Issue:** The Header lacks a hamburger menu. There is no way for mobile users to switch between main pages (About, Projects, Services) without scrolling to the footer.
- **Impact:** High. Frustrating navigation experience for mobile users.
- **Solution:** Implement a responsive hamburger menu in the Header.

### ⚠️ Visual: Chat Trigger Size & Position
- **Issue:** The floating chat bubble is excessively large and overlaps content in the bottom-right corner, especially on 360px screens.
- **Impact:** Medium. Obscures footer links and card details.
- **Solution:** Reduce the size of the chat bubble for mobile and add more bottom/right padding.

---

## 3. Page-By-Page Audit

### [1] Landing Page
- **Our Process Section:** Social icons overlap the section title and process steps.
- **Impact Section:** Stats like "Projects Completed" are partially obscured.
- **Community Section:** Contains redundant text "Join join now".
- **Footer CTA:** Typo found: "Let's Get Start" (Should be "Started").
- **Dummy Content:** "jvylhjihlv ncx m" found in community section.

### [2] About Page
- **Hero Section:** Horizontal margins are too narrow (text touches screen edges).
- **"Ready to Get Started":** Contains placeholder text "fn cx" and "f xc".
- **Typography:** "Numbers that speak volumes" is too large, causing unbalanced line breaks.

### [3] Projects & Project Details
- **Projects Page:** "Latest Projects solutions" (lowercase/unbalanced title).
- **Project Details:** The title repeats as H1 and H2 immediately after.
- **Image Scaling:** Project covers sometimes cut off important visual elements due to fixed aspect ratios.

### [4] Services & Service Details
- **Typo:** Global misspelling of **"devolopment"** in badges, titles, and slugs.
- **Service Cards:** Tags contain garbage data like "tjdngcv".
- **Detail Page:** Internal branding logo overlaps the service title text.

### [5] Shared Components
- **Navbar:** Lacks responsive padding; Logo and "Get in Touch" buttons are cramped.
- **Footer:** Improper vertical stacking; social icons overlap the "By QYNTA" text.
- **Popups:** The "Get in Touch" popup has excessive vertical white space and poor alignment on 360px widths.

---

## 4. Prioritized Recommendations

| Priority | Issue | Solution |
| :--- | :--- | :--- |
| **P0** | Social Sidebar Overlap | `display: none;` on mobile. |
| **P0** | Missing Mobile Menu | Implement Hamburger menu. |
| **P1** | Typo/Copy Corrections | Fix "devolopment", "Start", and placeholder text. |
| **P1** | Footer Layout | Use Flexbox/Stack for mobile footer. |
| **P2** | Typography Scaling | Use `clamp()` or media queries for H1/H2 sizes. |
| **P2** | Chat Trigger | Shrink chat bubble for mobile screens. |

---
